1:1 COMMENT "# ifnarrow.z - Flow narrowing from arm predicates in `if`"
1:58 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# A bare arm predicate in an if condition narrows its subject: the then"
3:72 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# branch knows the value holds the arm (bare name IS the payload, like a"
4:73 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# match arm); the else branch and later else-if clauses know it does not"
5:73 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# (the arm is excluded; when one arm remains the subject collapses to"
6:70 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# the payload -- the bare name reads it, exactly as in a match arm; the"
7:72 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# same collapse applies to a match else over one remaining arm). Negated"
8:73 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# forms `(x.a) == false` and `x.a.false` flip the two sides. Every bare"
9:72 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# conjunct of a `when` chain narrows in its then branch."
10:57 EOL "\n"
